Thai Red Curry

=== Req (4portionen): ===
300 g Sojageschnetzeltes
400ml Kokosmilch
Frischer Koreander
Frischer Basilikum
120g Prinzessbohnen
120g Süßkartoffel
Limettensaft

Ingwer
Gemüsebrühe
Fischsauce
Knoblauch
Kaffir-Limettenblätter 
Currypaste (Mae Ploy)
Palmzucker
ZitronengrasPaste
Brokkoli
2 Karotten

=== Zutaten für 4 Portionen: ===
4 EL Currypaste
2 	Schalotte(n)
2 	Knoblauchzehe(n)
300 g Sojageschnetzeltes
400 ml 	Kokosmilch
250 ml leichte Gemüsebrühe
120g Prinzessbohnen
120g Süßkartoffel
120g Brokkoli
2 Karotten
1 EL Zitronengraspaste
1 EL 	Fischsauce
1 EL 	Palmzucker
2 TL Ingwer

1 große Chilischote
5 Kaffir-Limettenblätter
Koriander - Samen

Frischer Koreander, Basilikum

=== Zubereitung ===


Heat oil in a large heavy based skillet over medium high heat.
Add curry paste and Extras (if using jar paste) and cook for about 2 minutes so it "dries out"
Dann Sojageschnetzeltes Abtrocknen/Tupfen und 3 min mit Anbraten

Add Gemüsebrühe broth and stir to dissolve paste. Simmer rapidly for 3 minutes or until liquid reduces by half.
Add coconut milk, lime leaves, sugar and fish sauce. 
Simmer for about 8- 10 minutes or until Sauce reduces, the chicken is cooked and the sauce is almost at the thickness you want.
Do a taste test. Add more fish sauce (or even shrimp paste) to add more saltiness, sugar for sweetness.
Add pumpkin and beans, 

Stir through a handful of Thai basil leaves.
